1
00:00:09,468 --> 00:00:11,094
(PHONE RINGING)

2
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:17,476
I said, no.

3
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:21,355
A sapphire waterfall.
It's a waterfall made of sapphires!

4
00:00:21,438 --> 00:00:23,106
This enormous jewel
the size of a glacier

5
00:00:23,232 --> 00:00:26,360
reaches the Cliffs of Oblivion and then
shatters into sapphires at the edge,

6
00:00:26,443 --> 00:00:29,488
then fall 100,000 feet
into a crystal ravine.

7
00:00:29,571 --> 00:00:33,617
-I bet you say that to all the girls.
-Oh, come on. They're boarding now.

8
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,787
It's no fun if I see it on me own.
Four hours, that's all it'll take.

9
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:38,914
No. That's four hours there
and four hours back.

10
00:00:38,997 --> 00:00:42,543
That's like a school trip.
I'd rather go sunbathing.

11
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:45,504
You be careful. That's extonic sunlight.

12
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:49,883
Oh, I'm safe. It says in the brochure
this glass is 15 feet thick.

13
00:00:49,967 --> 00:00:51,385
All right. I give up.

14
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:54,471
I'll be back for dinner. We'll try that
anti gravity restaurant, with bibs.

15
00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:58,767
That's a date. Well, not a date.
Oh, you know what I mean. Oh, get off.

16
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:00,310
-See you later.
-0j!

17
00:01:00,435 --> 00:01:02,145
And you be careful, all right?

18
00:01:02,271 --> 00:01:04,815
Nah! Taking a big space truck
with a bunch of strangers

19
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:09,111
across a diamond planet called Midnight?
What could possibly go wrong?

20
00:01:09,278 --> 00:01:11,321
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

21
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:50,611
HOSTESS: Complimentary juice pack
and complimentary headphones.

22
00:01:50,694 --> 00:01:52,696
WOMAN: Just the headphones, please.

23
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,281
There you go.

24
00:01:55,407 --> 00:01:58,118
That's the headphones
for channels 1 to 36.

25
00:01:58,201 --> 00:02:01,246
Mobile link for 3D vidgames,
complimentary earplugs,

26
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:03,749
complimentary slippers,
complimentary juice pack

27
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:05,250
and complimentary peanuts.

28
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:07,669
I must warn you that some
products may contain nuts.

29
00:02:07,753 --> 00:02:11,131
-That'd be the peanuts.
-Enjoy your trip.

30
00:02:11,214 --> 00:02:13,717
Oh, I can't wait. Allons-y.

31
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:17,095
-I'm sorry?
-It's French for "let's go".

32
00:02:17,179 --> 00:02:18,639
Fascinating.

33
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:22,517
-Headphones for channels 1 to 36...
-No, thank you. Not for us.

34
00:02:22,601 --> 00:02:24,561
Earplugs, please. Thank you.

35
00:02:24,728 --> 00:02:28,607
They call it the sapphire waterfall,
but it's no such thing.

36
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:30,776
Sapphire's an aluminium oxide,

37
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:34,738
but the glacier is just a compound
silicon with iron pigmentation.

38
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:36,823
-Juice packs?
-Oh, thank you.

39
00:02:36,907 --> 00:02:39,368
-Yes, certainly.
-And the pills.

40
00:02:39,451 --> 00:02:42,454
All measured out for you. There you go.

41
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:47,000
-Hobbes. Professor Winfold Hobbes.
-I'm the Doctor. Hello.

42
00:02:47,084 --> 00:02:49,878
-It's my 14th time.
-Oh, my first.

43
00:02:49,961 --> 00:02:53,840
-And I'm Dee Dee. Dee Dee Blasco.
-Don't bother the man.

44
00:02:53,924 --> 00:02:55,926
Where's my water bottle?

45
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:58,345
...complimentary slippers,
complimentary juice pack

46
00:02:58,428 --> 00:02:59,846
and complimentary peanuts.

47
00:02:59,930 --> 00:03:03,350
I must warn you that some
products may contain nuts.

48
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:07,813
Don't be silly. Come and sit with us.
Look, we get slippers.

49
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:10,357
-Jethro, do what your mother says.
-I'm sitting here.

50
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:13,193
Oh, he's ashamed of us,
but he doesn't mind us paying, does he?

51
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:15,028
Oh, don't you two start.

52
00:03:15,112 --> 00:03:16,947
Shall I save the juice pack
or have it now?

53
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,366
Look, peach and clementine.

54
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:21,910
Ladies and gentlemen
and variations thereupon,

55
00:03:21,993 --> 00:03:24,121
welcome on board the Crusader 50.

56
00:03:24,246 --> 00:03:28,542
If you would fasten your seat belts,
we'll be leaving any moment.

57
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:29,876
Doors.

58
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,461
(BEEPING)

59
00:03:32,504 --> 00:03:34,005
Shields down.

60
00:03:38,427 --> 00:03:42,305
I'm afraid the view is shielded
until we reach the Waterfall Palace.

61
00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:43,849
Also, a reminder.

62
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:48,979
Midnight has no air, so please
don't touch the exterior door seals.

63
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:53,191
Fire exit at the rear
and should we need to use it, you first.

64
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:57,487
Now I will hand you over to Driver joe.

65
00:03:57,654 --> 00:03:59,114
Driver Joe at the wheel.

66
00:03:59,197 --> 00:04:01,408
There's been a diamond fall
at the Winter Witch Canyon,

67
00:04:01,491 --> 00:04:05,120
so we'll be taking a slight detour,
as you'll see on the map.

68
00:04:05,203 --> 00:04:08,582
The journey covers 500 kliks
to the multifaceted coast.

69
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:11,418
Duration is estimated at four hours.

70
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:13,336
Thank you for travelling with us

71
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:17,257
and, as they used to say
in the olden days, "Wagons roll.”

72
00:04:19,009 --> 00:04:20,385
(BEEPING)

73
00:04:24,848 --> 00:04:28,226
For your entertainment, we have
the music channel playing retrovids

74
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:30,061
of Earth classics.

75
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:37,903
Also, the latest artistic installation
from Ludovic Klein.

76
00:04:40,447 --> 00:04:43,241
Plus for the youngsters, a rare treat.

77
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:45,535
The animation archives.

78
00:04:45,702 --> 00:04:48,705
Four hours of fun time. Enjoy.

79
00:04:52,042 --> 00:04:56,213
(MUSIC, ANIMATION
AND ART EXHIBITION ALL BLARING)

80
00:04:57,714 --> 00:05:01,218
# Do it, do it again
Do it, do it again... #

81
00:05:14,356 --> 00:05:15,899
(MUSIC STOPS)

82
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:20,570
Well, that's a mercy.

83
00:05:20,737 --> 00:05:25,367
Uh, I do apologise, ladies and gentlemen
and variations thereupon.

84
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:27,994
We seem to have had a failure
of the entertainment system.

85
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,996
-Oh!
-Well, what do we do?

86
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:34,125
We've got four hours of this?
Four hours of just sitting here?

87
00:05:34,209 --> 00:05:37,921
Tell you what. We'll have to
talk to each other instead.

88
00:05:45,762 --> 00:05:47,430
(ALL LAUGHING)

89
00:05:48,265 --> 00:05:50,308
So Biff said, "I'm going swimming."

90
00:05:50,392 --> 00:05:53,687
Oh, I was all ready.
Trunks and everything. Noseplug.

91
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:56,273
He had this little nose plug.
You should have seen him.

92
00:05:56,398 --> 00:05:59,943
And I went marching up to the lifequard,
and he was a Shamboni,

93
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:03,363
-you know, with those big foreheads.
-Great big forehead!

94
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:08,785
And I said, "Where's the pool?”
And he said, "The pool is abstract.”

95
00:06:10,745 --> 00:06:13,373
-It wasn't a real pool!
-It was a concept.

96
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:17,002
-And you were wearing your nose plug?
-I was like this.

97
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:26,303
I'm just a second year student,

98
00:06:26,428 --> 00:06:29,222
but I wrote a paper on
the lost moon of Poosh.

99
00:06:29,306 --> 00:06:31,308
Professor Hobbes read it, liked it,

100
00:06:31,433 --> 00:06:33,643
took me on as researcher,
just for the holidays.

101
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:35,770
Well, he said researcher,

102
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:38,398
but most of the time
he's got me fetching and carrying.

103
00:06:38,481 --> 00:06:39,858
But it's all good experience.

104
00:06:39,941 --> 00:06:42,319
-And did they ever find it?
-Find what?

105
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:45,614
-The lost moon of Poosh.
-No, not yet.

106
00:06:45,697 --> 00:06:48,783
Well, maybe that'll be
your great discovery one day.

107
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:51,494
-Here's to Poosh.
-Poosh.

108
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:57,250
No, no. I'm with this
friend of mine, Donna.

109
00:06:57,334 --> 00:06:59,377
She stayed behind in the Leisure Palace.
You?

110
00:06:59,461 --> 00:07:01,171
No. It's just me.

111
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:04,674
Oh, I've done plenty of that,
travelling on my own.

112
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:07,761
I love it.
Do what you want, go anywhere.

113
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:10,305
I'm still getting used to it.

114
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:13,725
I've found myself single
rather recently, not by choice.

115
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:16,478
-What happened?
-Oh, the usual.

116
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:19,773
She needed her own space, as they say.

117
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:24,361
A different galaxy, in fact.
I reckon that's enough space, don't you?

118
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:25,654
Yeah.

119
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:30,241
I had a friend who went to
a different universe.

120
00:07:30,325 --> 00:07:35,080
-Well, what's this? Chicken or beef?
-I think it's both.

121
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:44,381
So this is Midnight.
Do you see? Bombarded by the sun.

122
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:48,426
Extonic rays, raw galvanic radiation.

123
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,845
Dee Dee, next slide.

124
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,515
It's my pet project.

125
00:07:53,598 --> 00:07:58,770
Actually, I'm the first person
to research this because, you see,

126
00:08:01,773 --> 00:08:06,903
the history is fascinating
because there is no history.

127
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:10,573
There is no life in this entire system.
There couldn't be.

128
00:08:10,699 --> 00:08:13,493
Before the Leisure Palace Company
moved in,

129
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:17,747
no one had come here in all eternity.

130
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:20,041
No living thing.

131
00:08:23,169 --> 00:08:26,756
But how do you know?
I mean, if no one can go outside...

132
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:28,550
Oh, his imagination. Here we go.

133
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,635
-He's got a point, though.
-Exactly.

134
00:08:30,719 --> 00:08:35,432
We look upon this world through glass,
safe inside our metal box.

135
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:39,144
Even the Leisure Palace
was lowered down from orbit.

136
00:08:39,269 --> 00:08:44,774
And here we are now, crossing Midnight,
but never touching it.

137
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:47,819
(BANGING AND RATTLING)

138
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:51,072
We've stopped.

139
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:55,452
Have we stopped?

140
00:08:55,577 --> 00:08:58,246
-BIFF: Are we there?
-We can't be. It's too soon.

141
00:08:58,329 --> 00:09:01,875
HOBBES: No, they don't stop.
Crusader vehicles never stop.

142
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:06,087
If you could just return to your seats,
it's just a small delay.

143
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:12,302
Well, may be just a pit stop.

144
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:16,264
There's no pit to stop in.
I've been on this expedition 14 times.

145
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:17,640
They never stop.

146
00:09:17,724 --> 00:09:21,519
Well, evidently we have stopped,
so there's no point in denying it.

147
00:09:21,644 --> 00:09:22,979
We've broken down.

148
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:25,231
-Thanks, Jethro.
-In the middle of nowhere.

149
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:26,775
That's enough. Now stop it.

150
00:09:26,858 --> 00:09:29,486
Ladies and gentlemen
and variations thereupon,

151
00:09:29,611 --> 00:09:33,323
we're just experiencing a short delay.

152
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:35,533
The driver needs to stabilise
the engine feeds.

153
00:09:35,658 --> 00:09:39,162
It's perfectly routine, so if you
could just stay in your seats...

154
00:09:39,287 --> 00:09:41,998
-No, I'm sorry, sir, I...
-There you go. Engine expert. Two ticks.

155
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:42,624
Sorry, if you could just sit down...
You're not supposed to be in there!

156
00:09:42,624 --> 00:09:45,835
Sorry, if you could just sit down...
You're not supposed to be in there!

157
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,337
Sorry. If you could return
to your seat, sir.

158
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,547
Company insurance. Let's see
if we can get an early assessment.

159
00:09:49,631 --> 00:09:51,424
So what's the problem, Driver Joe?

160
00:09:51,508 --> 00:09:53,927
We're stabilising the engine feeds.
Won't take long.

161
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:57,764
Um, no, because that's the engine feed,
that line there, and it's fine.

162
00:09:57,847 --> 00:10:00,600
And it's a micro petrol engine, so
stabilising doesn't make sense, does it?

163
00:10:00,683 --> 00:10:03,853
Sorry, I'm a doctor. I'm very clever.
So what's wrong?

164
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:06,022
We've just stopped.
Look, all systems fine.

165
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:09,109
Everything's working,
but we're not moving.

166
00:10:09,192 --> 00:10:12,153
Yeah, you're right.
No faults. And who are you?

167
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:14,823
Claude. I'm the mechanic, trainee.

168
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:17,951
-Nice to meet you.
-I've sent a distress signal.

169
00:10:18,076 --> 00:10:20,120
They should dispatch a rescue truck,
top speed.

170
00:10:20,203 --> 00:10:22,956
-How long till they get here?
-About an hour.

171
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:27,377
Well, since we're waiting,
should we take a look outside?

172
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:28,670
Uh...

173
00:10:29,838 --> 00:10:31,506
Lift the screen a bit.

174
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:34,717
It's 100 percent extonic out there.
We'd be vapourised.

175
00:10:34,801 --> 00:10:37,804
No! Those windows are Finitoglass.
They'll give you a couple of minutes.

176
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:40,723
Go on. Live a little.

177
00:10:49,732 --> 00:10:51,526
CLAUDE: Wow.

178
00:10:56,114 --> 00:10:58,449
DOCTOR: That is beautiful.

179
00:10:58,575 --> 00:11:01,661
CLAUDE: Look at all those diamonds,
poisoned by the sun.

180
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:04,956
-No one can ever touch them.
-Joe, you said we took a detour.

181
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:08,168
-Just about 40 clicks to the west.
-Is that a recognised path?

182
00:11:08,251 --> 00:11:11,504
No, it's a new one.
The computer worked it out on automatic.

183
00:11:11,588 --> 00:11:13,631
So we're the first.

184
00:11:13,715 --> 00:11:17,302
This piece of ground,
no one's ever been here before.

185
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:23,099
-Not in the whole of recorded history.
-Did you just...

186
00:11:24,976 --> 00:11:27,979
-No, sorry. It was nothing.
-What did you see?

187
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:32,775
Just there, that ridge.
Like a shadow, just for a second.

188
00:11:32,859 --> 00:11:34,277
What sort of shadow?

189
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:35,695
(ALARM BEEPING)

190
00:11:35,778 --> 00:11:38,072
Extonic rising. Shields down.

191
00:11:40,491 --> 00:11:44,287
-Look, look, there it is! There it is!
-Where!

192
00:11:44,412 --> 00:11:45,747
What was it?

193
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:49,626
Just something shifting,
something sort of dark,

194
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:51,711
like it was running.

195
00:11:51,794 --> 00:11:55,131
-Running which way?
-Towards us.

196
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:56,883
Right, Doctor. Back to your seat.

197
00:11:56,966 --> 00:11:59,886
And, uh, not a word.
Rescue's on its way.

198
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:01,679
If you could close the door. Thank you.

199
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:09,229
What did they say? Did they tell you?
What is it? What's wrong?

200
00:12:09,312 --> 00:12:11,564
Oh, just stabilising.
Happens all the time.

201
00:12:11,648 --> 00:12:15,568
I don't need this. I'm on a schedule.
This is completely unnecessary.

202
00:12:15,652 --> 00:12:18,029
Back to your seats. Thank you.

203
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:23,910
Excuse me, Doctor.

204
00:12:23,993 --> 00:12:25,828
They're micro petrol engines,
aren't they?

205
00:12:25,912 --> 00:12:29,082
-Now, don't bother the man.
-My father was a mechanic.

206
00:12:29,207 --> 00:12:32,585
Micropetrol doesn't stabilise.
What does stabilise mean?

207
00:12:32,669 --> 00:12:35,255
Well, a bit of flim-flam.
Don't worry, they're sorting it out.

208
00:12:35,338 --> 00:12:38,299
-So it's not the engine?
-Just a little pause, that's all.

209
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:40,677
-How much air have we got?
-Professor, it's fine.

210
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,011
-What did he say?
-Nothing.

211
00:12:42,095 --> 00:12:44,389
VAL: Are we running out of air?
HOBBES: I was just speculating.

212
00:12:44,514 --> 00:12:46,182
Is that right, miss?
Are we running out of air?

213
00:12:46,266 --> 00:12:48,893
-Is that what the captain said?
-If you could all just remain calm...

214
00:12:48,977 --> 00:12:50,603
-How much air have we got?
-Mum, just stop it.

215
00:12:50,687 --> 00:12:53,273
-Everything is under control.
-It doesn't look like it.

216
00:12:53,356 --> 00:12:54,857
-He said it!
-It's fine!

217
00:12:54,983 --> 00:12:57,193
(ALL SHOUTING)

218
00:13:00,530 --> 00:13:02,198
Quiet!

219
00:13:07,287 --> 00:13:09,122
Thank you.

220
00:13:09,205 --> 00:13:12,834
Now, if you care to listen
to my good friend Dee Dee...

221
00:13:14,377 --> 00:13:16,212
Oh, um...

222
00:13:16,713 --> 00:13:19,590
It's just that, well,
the air's on a circular filter,

223
00:13:19,716 --> 00:13:22,552
so we could stay breathing for 10 years.

224
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:24,721
DOCTOR: There you go.

225
00:13:24,846 --> 00:13:28,641
And I've spoken to the captain.
I can guarantee you, everything's fine.

226
00:13:28,725 --> 00:13:30,393
(POUNDING)

227
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:37,025
What was that?

228
00:13:37,108 --> 00:13:40,862
It must be the metal.
We're cooling down. It's just settling.

229
00:13:40,945 --> 00:13:42,405
Rocks. Could be rocks falling.

230
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:45,199
What I want to know is
how long do we have to sit here?

231
00:13:45,283 --> 00:13:46,951
(POUNDING)

232
00:13:47,035 --> 00:13:48,328
What is that?

233
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:50,121
-There's someone out there.
-Don't be ridiculous.

234
00:13:50,246 --> 00:13:51,497
Like I said, it could be rocks.

235
00:13:51,581 --> 00:13:54,083
We're out in the open.
Nothing could fall against the sides.

236
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:55,585
(POUNDING)

237
00:13:56,586 --> 00:13:59,922
-Knock, knock.
-Who's there?

238
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:10,767
Is there something out there?
Well, anyone?

239
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:12,310
(POUNDING)

240
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:14,020
What the hell is making that noise?

241
00:14:14,103 --> 00:14:17,398
I'm sorry, but the light
out there is extonic.

242
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:21,861
That means it would destroy
any living thing in a split second.

243
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:26,240
It is impossible for
someone to be outside.

244
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:31,037
(POUNDING)

245
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:33,247
Well, what the hell is that, then?

246
00:14:33,331 --> 00:14:36,459
Sir, you really should
get back to your seat.

247
00:14:41,047 --> 00:14:42,340
Hello.

248
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:43,841
(POUNDING)

249
00:14:46,469 --> 00:14:47,970
It's moving.

250
00:14:52,350 --> 00:14:53,726
(RATTLING)

251
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:55,103
It's trying the door.

252
00:14:55,186 --> 00:14:58,981
There is no "it".
There's nothing out there. Can't be.

253
00:14:59,107 --> 00:15:00,483
(CLANGING)

254
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:06,864
(BANGING)

255
00:15:13,329 --> 00:15:15,415
(POUNDING)

256
00:15:15,498 --> 00:15:16,999
That's the entrance. Can it get in?

257
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:19,460
No. That door's on 200-weight hydronics.

258
00:15:19,544 --> 00:15:23,297
-Stop it. Don't encourage them.
-Well, what do you think it is?

259
00:15:23,381 --> 00:15:26,175
-VAL: Biff, don't!
-Mr Kane, better not.

260
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:28,719
It's cast iron, that door.

261
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:32,098
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

262
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:35,268
Three times! Did you hear that?
It did it three times.

263
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:36,853
It did it three times!

264
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:38,563
All right, all right,
everyone calm down.

265
00:15:38,688 --> 00:15:41,065
Yeah, but it answered. It answered.

266
00:15:41,149 --> 00:15:43,443
Don't tell me that thing's not alive.
It answered him.

267
00:15:43,526 --> 00:15:44,777
(BANGING)

268
00:15:44,861 --> 00:15:48,114
I really must insist
you get back to your seats!

269
00:15:48,197 --> 00:15:50,658
No, don't just stand there
telling us the rules!

270
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:54,203
You're the hostess!
You're supposed to do something!

271
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,756
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

272
00:16:05,882 --> 00:16:07,675
What the hell's making that noise?

273
00:16:07,758 --> 00:16:12,388
She said she'd get me.
Stop it! Make it stop! Make it stop!

274
00:16:12,472 --> 00:16:15,850
Don't just stand there looking at me.
It's not my fault. He started it with...

275
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:18,019
-Calm down!
-...he made it worse!

276
00:16:18,144 --> 00:16:20,563
Why couldn't you leave it alone?
Stop staring at me!

277
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:23,524
-The rescue's coming...
-Calm down!

278
00:16:23,608 --> 00:16:25,067
(POUNDING)

279
00:16:27,069 --> 00:16:29,197
It's coming for me.

280
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:32,283
Oh, it's coming for me.
It's coming for me!

281
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:35,328
It's coming for me.

282
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:37,914
It's coming for me!

283
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,874
(POUNDING)

284
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:41,751
Get out of there!

285
00:16:58,976 --> 00:17:00,728
(ALL GRUNTING)

286
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:04,398
All right? Okay.

287
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:13,616
Arms, legs, neck, head, nose. I'm fine.

288
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:15,785
Everyone else?

289
00:17:17,954 --> 00:17:20,289
How are we? Everyone all right?

290
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:23,125
HOBBES: Earthquake, must be.

291
00:17:23,251 --> 00:17:26,420
But that's impossible.
The ground is fixed. It's solid.

292
00:17:26,546 --> 00:17:28,798
We've got torches.
Everyone take a torch.

293
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:31,425
They're in the back of the seats.

294
00:17:34,804 --> 00:17:37,640
Oh, Jethro. Sweetheart, come here.

295
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:40,059
Never mind me. What about her?

296
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,730
VAL: What's happened to the seats?
BIFF: Who did that?

297
00:17:44,814 --> 00:17:47,108
VAL: They've been ripped up.

298
00:17:48,693 --> 00:17:51,821
It's all right, it's all right,
it's all right, it's over.

299
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:55,283
We're still alive.
Look, the wall's still intact, eh?

300
00:17:55,366 --> 00:17:57,368
-HOSTESS: Joe, Claude?
-We're safe.

301
00:17:57,493 --> 00:17:59,579
Driver Joe, can you hear me?

302
00:17:59,662 --> 00:18:03,332
I'm not getting any response.
The intercom must be down.

303
00:18:11,007 --> 00:18:12,383
What happened? What was that?

304
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:15,303
Is it the driver?
Have we lost the driver?

305
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:17,430
-The cabin's gone.
-Don't be ridiculous.

306
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:19,348
It can't be gone. How can it be gone?

307
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:21,517
-You saw it.
-There was nothing there.

308
00:18:21,601 --> 00:18:23,978
-Like it was ripped away.
-What are you doing?

309
00:18:24,061 --> 00:18:26,397
That's better. A little bit of light.
Thank you. Motto bene.

310
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:27,690
Do you know what you're doing?

311
00:18:27,815 --> 00:18:29,525
The cabin's gone.
You better leave that wall alone.

312
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:32,153
-The cabin can't be gone.
-No, it's safe.

313
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:35,239
Any rupture would automatically
seal itself.

314
00:18:36,866 --> 00:18:39,201
Unless something sliced it off.

315
00:18:40,453 --> 00:18:43,289
-You're right, the cabin's gone.
-But if it gets separated...

316
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:45,207
It loses integrity.

317
00:18:48,044 --> 00:18:50,921
I'm sorry. They've been reduced to dust.

318
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:53,716
The driver and the mechanic.

319
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:57,053
They sent a distress signal.
Help is on its way.

320
00:18:57,178 --> 00:19:00,556
They saved our lives.
We are gonna get out of here, I promise.

321
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:02,808
We're still alive
and they're gonna find us.

322
00:19:02,892 --> 00:19:04,727
Doctor, look at her.

323
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:09,982
Right, yeah, sorry.
Have we got a medical kit?

324
00:19:10,066 --> 00:19:12,568
JETHRO: Why won't she turn around?

325
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:18,658
-HOBBES: What's her name?
-Silvestry. Mrs Sky Silvestry.

326
00:19:20,242 --> 00:19:21,410
Sky?

327
00:19:22,328 --> 00:19:23,996
Can you hear me?

328
00:19:24,455 --> 00:19:26,165
You're all right.

329
00:19:28,334 --> 00:19:30,086
Can you move, Sky?

330
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:33,255
Just look at me.

331
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:39,929
That noise from outside, it's stopped.

332
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:44,266
-Well, thank God for that.
-But what if it's not outside any more?

333
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:47,770
-What if it's inside?
-Inside? Where?

334
00:19:48,771 --> 00:19:50,773
It was heading for her.

335
00:19:51,524 --> 00:19:52,775
Sky?

336
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:55,277
It's all right, Sky.

337
00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:59,949
Just want you to turn around, face me.

338
00:20:39,113 --> 00:20:40,197
Sky?

339
00:20:42,366 --> 00:20:43,492
Sky.

340
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:47,997
-Are you all right?
-Are you all right?

341
00:20:48,122 --> 00:20:50,332
-Are you hurt?
-Are you hurt?

342
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:53,502
-You don't have to talk.
-You don't have to talk.

343
00:20:53,627 --> 00:20:56,005
-I'm trying to help.
-I'm trying to help.

344
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:58,883
-My name's the Doctor.
-My name's the Doctor.

345
00:20:58,966 --> 00:21:01,427
-Okay, can you stop?
-Okay, can you stop?

346
00:21:01,552 --> 00:21:03,721
-I'd like you to stop.
-I'd like you to stop.

347
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:06,265
-Why's she doing that?
-Why's she doing that?

348
00:21:06,348 --> 00:21:07,600
-She's gone mad.
-She's gone mad.

349
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:08,893
-Stop it.
-Stop it.

350
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:10,227
-1 said, stop It.
-1 said, stop It.

351
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:12,104
-I don't think she can.
-I don't think she can.

352
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:14,607
-Now stop it. This isn't funny.
-Now stop it. This isn't funny.

353
00:21:14,690 --> 00:21:17,109
-Shh, shh, shh, all of you.
-Shh, shh, shh, all of you.

354
00:21:17,193 --> 00:21:18,819
-My name's Jethro.
-My name's Jethro.

355
00:21:18,903 --> 00:21:23,073
-Jethro, leave it. Just shut up.
-Jethro, leave it. Just shut up.

356
00:21:28,454 --> 00:21:31,874
-Why are you repeating?
-Why are you repeating?

357
00:21:34,543 --> 00:21:37,630
-What is that? Learning?
-What is that? Learning?

358
00:21:37,713 --> 00:21:39,548
-Copying?
-Copying?

359
00:21:41,926 --> 00:21:43,928
-Absorbing.
-Absorbing.

360
00:21:47,181 --> 00:21:48,557
The square root of piis 1.77...

361
00:21:48,641 --> 00:21:53,729
BOTH: ...of pi is 1.77245385090551602729

362
00:21:53,854 --> 00:21:57,358
8167483341.

363
00:21:57,441 --> 00:21:59,026
Wow.

364
00:22:02,863 --> 00:22:05,366
-But that's impossible.
-But that's impossible.

365
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:07,201
-She couldn't repeat it.
-She couldn't repeat it.

366
00:22:07,284 --> 00:22:08,619
-Tell her to stop.
-Tell her to stop.

367
00:22:08,744 --> 00:22:10,412
-She's driving me mad.
-She's driving me mad.

368
00:22:10,496 --> 00:22:11,664
-Just make her stop.
-Just make her stop.

369
00:22:11,747 --> 00:22:13,040
-Stop staring at me.
-Stop staring at me.

370
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:16,669
(ALL TALKING AT ONCE)

371
00:22:18,546 --> 00:22:20,923
Now, stop. Stop it, all of you.

372
00:22:22,383 --> 00:22:24,885
(ALL TALKING)

373
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:32,101
-666.
-666.

374
00:22:35,813 --> 00:22:37,356
Make her stop.

375
00:22:37,439 --> 00:22:39,108
(HUMMING)

376
00:22:42,444 --> 00:22:46,448
-That's the backup system.
-Well, that's a bit better.

377
00:22:46,532 --> 00:22:48,450
What about the rescue?
How long's it going to take?

378
00:22:48,534 --> 00:22:51,287
About 60 minutes, that's all.

379
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:54,665
Then I suggest we all calm down.

380
00:22:54,957 --> 00:22:57,126
This panic isn't helping.

381
00:22:57,251 --> 00:23:00,713
And that poor woman
is evidently in a state of...

382
00:23:00,796 --> 00:23:02,756
(ECHO) ...self-induced hysteria.
We should leave her...

383
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,133
Doctor.

384
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:06,218
I know.

385
00:23:06,594 --> 00:23:08,512
Doctor, now step back.

386
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:12,182
-I think you should leave her...
-Leave her...

387
00:23:12,308 --> 00:23:13,851
Alone.

388
00:23:16,854 --> 00:23:18,564
What's she doing?

389
00:23:19,815 --> 00:23:23,027
-How could she do that?
-She's talking with you.

390
00:23:23,444 --> 00:23:24,820
And with me.

391
00:23:24,945 --> 00:23:27,823
Oh, my God! Biff, what's she doing?

392
00:23:27,907 --> 00:23:29,575
She's repeating.

393
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,660
At exactly the same time.

394
00:23:31,785 --> 00:23:33,162
That's impossible.

395
00:23:33,287 --> 00:23:34,955
There's not even a delay.

396
00:23:35,039 --> 00:23:36,749
Oh, man, that is weird.

397
00:23:36,832 --> 00:23:39,251
I think you should all be
very, very quiet.

398
00:23:39,335 --> 00:23:41,879
-Have you got that?
-How's she doing it?

399
00:23:41,962 --> 00:23:44,173
-Mrs Kane, please be quiet.
-How can she do that?

400
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:46,342
She's got my voice! She's got my words!

401
00:23:46,467 --> 00:23:49,595
Darling, be quiet. Hush, now, hush.

402
00:23:49,678 --> 00:23:50,888
She's doing it to me.

403
00:23:51,013 --> 00:23:53,891
Just stop it.
All of you, stop it, please.

404
00:24:00,981 --> 00:24:04,068
Now then, Sky, are you Sky?

405
00:24:04,735 --> 00:24:08,197
Is Sky still in there? Mrs Silvestry?

406
00:24:10,866 --> 00:24:15,245
You know exactly what I'm going to say.
How are you doing that?

407
00:24:17,831 --> 00:24:19,875
Roast beef.

408
00:24:20,042 --> 00:24:21,794
Bananas.

409
00:24:22,044 --> 00:24:24,296
The Medusa Cascade.

410
00:24:27,174 --> 00:24:28,300
Bang!

411
00:24:28,384 --> 00:24:31,553
Rose Tyler, Martha Jones,
Donna Noble, Tardis.

412
00:24:33,889 --> 00:24:36,934
Shamble, bobble, dibble, dooble.

413
00:24:38,268 --> 00:24:42,064
Oh, Doctor, you're so handsome.
Yes, I am. Thank you.

414
00:24:43,774 --> 00:24:46,652
A K Mo.

415
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:56,662
First she repeats, then she catches up.
What's the next stage?

416
00:24:56,745 --> 00:24:58,205
Next stage of what?

417
00:24:58,288 --> 00:25:02,334
It's not her, is it?
That's not Mrs Silvestry any more.

418
00:25:02,418 --> 00:25:04,336
I don't think so, no.

419
00:25:05,587 --> 00:25:07,297
(SOBBING)

420
00:25:07,881 --> 00:25:12,428
I think the more we talk,
the more she learns.

421
00:25:12,511 --> 00:25:17,141
Now, I'm all for education,
but in this case, maybe not.

422
00:25:17,266 --> 00:25:20,102
Let's just move back.
Come on, come with me.

423
00:25:20,185 --> 00:25:22,146
Everyone, get back, all of you,
as far as you can.

424
00:25:22,271 --> 00:25:24,106
Doctor, make her stop.

425
00:25:24,189 --> 00:25:26,275
Val, come with me.
Come to the back. Stop looking at her.

426
00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:29,445
Come on. Jethro, you, too.
Everyone, come on.

427
00:25:29,778 --> 00:25:31,363
50 minutes, that's all we need.

428
00:25:31,447 --> 00:25:35,784
50 minutes till the rescue arrives and
she's not exactly strong. Look at her.

429
00:25:35,868 --> 00:25:40,247
-All she's got is our voices.
-I can't look at her. It's those eyes.

430
00:25:45,044 --> 00:25:47,546
We must not look at goblin men.

431
00:25:50,132 --> 00:25:54,303
-What's that supposed to mean?
-It's a poem, Christina Rossetti.

432
00:25:59,975 --> 00:26:03,020
"We must not look at goblin men,
We must not buy their fruits:

433
00:26:03,103 --> 00:26:07,149
"Who knows upon what soil they fed
Their hungry thirsty roots?"

434
00:26:08,567 --> 00:26:12,112
-Actually, I don't think that's helping.
-She's not a goblin or a monster.

435
00:26:12,196 --> 00:26:15,491
-She's just a very sick woman.
-Maybe that's why it went for her.

436
00:26:15,616 --> 00:26:18,160
-There is no "it".
-Think about it, though.

437
00:26:18,243 --> 00:26:21,330
That knocking went all the way
around the bus until it found her.

438
00:26:21,413 --> 00:26:24,500
And she was the most
scared out of all of us.

439
00:26:25,084 --> 00:26:29,129
Maybe that's what it needed.
That's how it got in.

440
00:26:29,213 --> 00:26:34,635
For the last time, nothing can
live on the surface of Midnight.

441
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,720
Professor, I'm glad
you've got an absolute definition

442
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:40,516
of life in the universe, but perhaps
the universe has got ideas of its own.

443
00:26:40,599 --> 00:26:42,559
Now trust me, I've got previous.

444
00:26:42,643 --> 00:26:46,647
I think there might well be some
consciousness inside Mrs Silvestry,

445
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:49,191
but maybe she's still in there
and it's our job to help her.

446
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:52,611
-You can help, but I'm not going near.
-No, I've got to stay back.

447
00:26:52,694 --> 00:26:55,572
'Cause if she's copying us, then
maybe the final stage is becoming us.

448
00:26:55,656 --> 00:26:58,534
I don't want her becoming me
or things could get a whole lot worse.

449
00:26:58,659 --> 00:27:01,662
-Oh, like you're so special.
-As it happens, yes, I am.

450
00:27:01,745 --> 00:27:04,331
So that's decided.
We stay back and we wait.

451
00:27:04,414 --> 00:27:08,043
When the rescue ship comes,
we can get her to hospital.

452
00:27:09,211 --> 00:27:11,713
We should throw her out.

453
00:27:12,464 --> 00:27:14,216
I beg your pardon?

454
00:27:16,051 --> 00:27:17,928
-Can we do that?
-Don't be ridiculous.

455
00:27:18,053 --> 00:27:21,265
That thing, whatever it is,
killed the driver and the mechanic

456
00:27:21,390 --> 00:27:22,933
and I don't think she's finished yet.

457
00:27:23,058 --> 00:27:26,019
-She can't even move.
-Look at her. Look at her eyes.

458
00:27:26,103 --> 00:27:29,231
She killed Joe and she killed Claude
and we're next.

459
00:27:29,356 --> 00:27:33,694
She's still doing it.
Just stop it! Stop talking! Stop it!

460
00:27:33,777 --> 00:27:36,905
-Biff, don't, sweetheart!
-But she won't stop!

461
00:27:37,531 --> 00:27:40,075
We can't throw her out, though.
We can't even open the doors.

462
00:27:40,159 --> 00:27:42,452
No one is getting thrown out.

463
00:27:50,252 --> 00:27:53,505
Yes, we can
'cause there's an air pressure seal.

464
00:27:53,589 --> 00:27:56,008
Like when you opened the cabin door,
you weren't pulled out.

465
00:27:56,091 --> 00:27:57,426
You had a couple of seconds

466
00:27:57,509 --> 00:27:59,970
'cause it takes the pressure wall
about six seconds to collapse.

467
00:28:00,053 --> 00:28:02,181
Well, six seconds exactly.

468
00:28:02,931 --> 00:28:05,559
That's enough time to throw someone out.

469
00:28:05,642 --> 00:28:07,644
Thanks, Dee Dee. Just what we needed.

470
00:28:07,769 --> 00:28:09,771
-Would it kill her outside?
-I don't know.

471
00:28:09,855 --> 00:28:11,940
But she's got a body now.
It'd certainly kill the physical...

472
00:28:12,024 --> 00:28:14,359
No one is killing anyone!

473
00:28:14,443 --> 00:28:17,196
I wouldn't risk the cabin door twice,
but we've got that one.

474
00:28:17,279 --> 00:28:19,698
All we need to do is grab
hold of her and throw her out.

475
00:28:19,781 --> 00:28:22,868
Now listen, all of you, for all we know
that's a brand-new life form over there

476
00:28:22,951 --> 00:28:25,996
and if it's come inside to discover us,
then what's it found?

477
00:28:26,079 --> 00:28:28,332
This little bunch of humans.

478
00:28:28,415 --> 00:28:30,751
What do you amount to? Murder?

479
00:28:31,335 --> 00:28:34,838
'Cause this is where you decide.
You decide who you are.

480
00:28:34,922 --> 00:28:37,841
Could you actually murder her,
any of you?

481
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:39,801
Really?

482
00:28:41,428 --> 00:28:43,680
Or are you better than that?

483
00:28:51,897 --> 00:28:53,273
I'd do it.

484
00:28:53,357 --> 00:28:54,608
-So would I.
-And me.

485
00:28:54,691 --> 00:28:56,151
-I think we should.
-What?

486
00:28:56,235 --> 00:28:57,945
-I want her out.
-You can't say that.

487
00:28:58,028 --> 00:28:59,738
I'm sorry,
but you said it yourself, Doctor.

488
00:28:59,821 --> 00:29:02,241
-She's growing in strength.
-That's not what I said.

489
00:29:02,324 --> 00:29:06,578
I wanna go home.
I'm sorry. I want to be safe.

490
00:29:06,662 --> 00:29:09,081
You'll be safe. Any minute now.
The rescue truck is on its way.

491
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:11,291
And what happens then, Doctor?

492
00:29:11,375 --> 00:29:13,627
If it takes that thing back
to the Leisure Palace,

493
00:29:13,710 --> 00:29:16,213
if that thing reaches civilisation,
what if it spreads?

494
00:29:16,296 --> 00:29:18,757
No, because when we get back to
the base, I'll be there to contain it.

495
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:20,092
You haven't done much so far.

496
00:29:20,175 --> 00:29:22,010
He's just standing at the back
with the rest of us.

497
00:29:22,094 --> 00:29:23,470
She's dangerous.

498
00:29:23,553 --> 00:29:26,890
It's my job to see that this vessel
is safe. We should get rid of her.

499
00:29:26,974 --> 00:29:30,936
Now hang on. I think perhaps
we're all going a little bit too far.

500
00:29:31,019 --> 00:29:34,064
-At last! Thank you.
-Two people are dead!

501
00:29:34,147 --> 00:29:36,024
Don't make it a third!

502
00:29:39,361 --> 00:29:41,196
Jethro, what do you say?

503
00:29:41,363 --> 00:29:42,823
-I'm not killing anyone.
-Thank you.

504
00:29:42,906 --> 00:29:44,908
-He's just a boy.
-What, so I don't get a vote?

505
00:29:44,992 --> 00:29:47,953
There isn't a vote.
It's not happening, ever!

506
00:29:48,662 --> 00:29:53,208
If you try to throw her out that door,
you'll have to get past me first.

507
00:29:55,669 --> 00:29:57,879
-Okay.
-Fine by me.

508
00:29:57,963 --> 00:30:00,507
Oh, now you're being stupid.
Just think about it.

509
00:30:00,590 --> 00:30:03,218
Could you actually take hold of someone
and throw them out of that door?

510
00:30:03,302 --> 00:30:04,469
Calling me a coward?

511
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:06,638
-Who put you in charge anyway?
-I'm sorry.

512
00:30:06,722 --> 00:30:10,058
-You're a doctor of what exactly?
-He wasn't even booked in.

513
00:30:10,142 --> 00:30:14,146
The rest of you, tickets in advance,
he just turned up out of the blue.

514
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:15,731
VAL: Where from?

515
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:18,233
I'm just travelling.
I'm a traveller, that's all.

516
00:30:18,358 --> 00:30:20,068
-Like an immigrant?
-Who were you talking to?

517
00:30:20,193 --> 00:30:22,821
Before you got on board, you were
talking to someone. Who was that?

518
00:30:22,904 --> 00:30:23,989
Just Donna. Just my friend.

519
00:30:24,072 --> 00:30:26,408
-What were you saying to her?
-He hasn't even told us his name.

520
00:30:26,491 --> 00:30:28,910
The thing is though, Doctor,
you've been loving this.

521
00:30:29,036 --> 00:30:30,579
Oh, Jethro, not you.

522
00:30:30,704 --> 00:30:33,749
No, but ever since all the trouble
has started, you've been loving it.

523
00:30:33,915 --> 00:30:37,669
It has to be said,
you do seem to have a certain glee.

524
00:30:37,753 --> 00:30:40,339
All right, I'm interested, yes.
I can't help it.

525
00:30:40,422 --> 00:30:44,176
'Cause whatever's inside her,
it's brand-new and that's fascinating.

526
00:30:44,259 --> 00:30:45,469
What, you wanted this to happen?

527
00:30:45,594 --> 00:30:47,304
-No!
-You were talking to her.

528
00:30:47,387 --> 00:30:49,348
All on your own, before all the trouble,
right at the front,

529
00:30:49,431 --> 00:30:52,267
you were talking to that Sky woman,
the two of you together.

530
00:30:52,392 --> 00:30:53,935
-I saw you!
-We all did.

531
00:30:54,019 --> 00:30:55,979
-You went into the cabin.
-What were you saying to her?

532
00:30:56,104 --> 00:30:57,647
-I was just talking.
-Saying what?

533
00:30:57,731 --> 00:30:59,691
You called us "humans”,
like you're not one of us.

534
00:30:59,775 --> 00:31:02,027
-That's what he said.
-And the wiring.

535
00:31:02,110 --> 00:31:04,196
He went into that panel
and opened up the wiring.

536
00:31:04,279 --> 00:31:06,573
-That was after.
-But how did you know what to do?

537
00:31:06,656 --> 00:31:08,492
Because I'm clever!

538
00:31:13,955 --> 00:31:15,415
I see.

539
00:31:15,499 --> 00:31:19,961
-Well, that makes things clear.
-And what are we, then? Idiots?

540
00:31:20,087 --> 00:31:22,839
-That's not what I meant.
-If you're clever, then what are we?

541
00:31:22,923 --> 00:31:25,092
You've been looking down on us
from the moment we walked in.

542
00:31:25,175 --> 00:31:27,719
Even if he goes,
he's practically volunteered.

543
00:31:27,803 --> 00:31:30,722
Oh, come on!
Just listen to yourselves, please!

544
00:31:30,806 --> 00:31:33,975
Do you mean... We throw him out as well.

545
00:31:42,150 --> 00:31:43,693
If we have to.

546
00:31:44,319 --> 00:31:46,196
Look, just...

547
00:31:46,321 --> 00:31:48,907
Hang on, sorry, yes, hold on, just...

548
00:31:49,741 --> 00:31:53,912
I know you're scared.
And so am I. Look at me, I am.

549
00:31:53,995 --> 00:31:58,333
But we have all got to calm down
and cool off and think.

550
00:31:58,417 --> 00:32:01,586
-Perhaps you could tell us your name.
-What does it matter?

551
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:05,298
-Then tell us.
-John Smith.

552
00:32:05,382 --> 00:32:07,467
-Your real name.
-He's lying. Look at his face.

553
00:32:07,551 --> 00:32:09,344
-His eyes are the same as hers.
-Why won't you tell us?

554
00:32:09,428 --> 00:32:10,512
It's a symptom.

555
00:32:10,595 --> 00:32:12,556
He's been lying to us
right from the start!

556
00:32:12,639 --> 00:32:14,558
No one's called John Smith.
Come off it!

557
00:32:14,683 --> 00:32:17,060
Listen to me right now
because you need me, all of you!

558
00:32:17,185 --> 00:32:19,479
If we are going to get out of this,
then you need me!

559
00:32:19,563 --> 00:32:22,065
So you keep saying. You've been
repeating yourself more than her.

560
00:32:22,149 --> 00:32:24,443
If anyone's in charge, it should
be the professor. He's the expert!

561
00:32:24,526 --> 00:32:26,945
Mum, just stop. Just look.

562
00:32:27,028 --> 00:32:29,322
-You keep out of this, Jethro.
-Look at her!

563
00:32:29,406 --> 00:32:30,949
She's stopped.

564
00:32:36,037 --> 00:32:37,456
-When did she...
-When did she...

565
00:32:37,539 --> 00:32:39,541
-No, she's still doing it.
-No, she's still doing it.

566
00:32:39,708 --> 00:32:41,418
She looks the same to me.

567
00:32:41,543 --> 00:32:44,171
No. She's stopped.

568
00:32:44,713 --> 00:32:48,091
-Look, I'm talking and she's not.
-BIFF: What about me? Is she...

569
00:32:48,175 --> 00:32:52,304
Look. Look at that.
She's not doing me. She's let me go.

570
00:32:52,387 --> 00:32:53,930
Mrs Silvestry?

571
00:32:56,057 --> 00:32:57,726
Nor me. Nothing.

572
00:32:59,060 --> 00:33:00,770
-Sky?
-Sky?

573
00:33:00,896 --> 00:33:02,397
-What are you doing?
-What are you doing?

574
00:33:02,564 --> 00:33:04,441
She's still doing him.

575
00:33:05,192 --> 00:33:08,069
Doctor, it's you.
She's only copying you.

576
00:33:09,488 --> 00:33:11,990
-Why me? Why are you doing this?
-Why me? Why are you doing this?

577
00:33:12,073 --> 00:33:14,326
VAL: She won't leave him alone.
Do you see?

578
00:33:14,409 --> 00:33:16,703
-I said so. She's with him.
-They're together.

579
00:33:16,828 --> 00:33:19,706
How do you explain it, Doctor?
If you're so clever...

580
00:33:19,789 --> 00:33:22,042
-I don't know.
-I don't know.

581
00:33:22,125 --> 00:33:24,294
-Sky, stop it.
-Sky, stop it.

582
00:33:24,419 --> 00:33:26,588
-I said, stop it. Just stop it.
-I said, stop it. Just stop it.

583
00:33:26,671 --> 00:33:28,715
Look at the two of them.

584
00:33:30,926 --> 00:33:34,888
BOTH: Mrs Silvestry,
I'm trying to understand.

585
00:33:34,971 --> 00:33:38,850
You've captured my speech.
What for?

586
00:33:38,934 --> 00:33:41,520
What do you need?

587
00:33:43,605 --> 00:33:46,441
You need my voice in particular.

588
00:33:46,525 --> 00:33:48,777
The cleverest voice in the room.

589
00:33:48,860 --> 00:33:52,697
Why? Because I'm the only one
who can help?

590
00:33:52,781 --> 00:33:54,699
Oh, I'd love that to be true.

591
00:33:54,783 --> 00:33:59,621
But your eyes,
they're saying something else.

592
00:33:59,704 --> 00:34:02,374
Listen to me, whatever you want,

593
00:34:02,457 --> 00:34:06,628
if it's Llife or form
or consciousness or voice,

594
00:34:06,711 --> 00:34:09,005
you don't have to steal it.

595
00:34:09,130 --> 00:34:12,676
You can find it without hurting anyone.

596
00:34:12,759 --> 00:34:14,803
And I'll help you.

597
00:34:14,886 --> 00:34:16,972
That's a promise.

598
00:34:17,097 --> 00:34:20,267
So, what do you think?

599
00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:25,146
SKY: Do we have a deal?
DOCTOR: Do we have a deal?

600
00:34:28,942 --> 00:34:31,570
-Hold on. Did she...
-She spoke first.

601
00:34:31,653 --> 00:34:35,073
-She can't have.
-She did. She spoke first.

602
00:34:37,325 --> 00:34:40,120
Oh, look at that.

603
00:34:40,245 --> 00:34:43,206
-Oh, look at that. I'm ahead of you.
-I'm ahead of you.

604
00:34:43,290 --> 00:34:44,916
Did you see?

605
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:47,669
She spoke before he did, definitely.

606
00:34:47,961 --> 00:34:49,671
He's copying her.

607
00:34:50,380 --> 00:34:52,299
Doctor, what's happening?

608
00:34:52,382 --> 00:34:54,509
SKY: I think it's moved.

609
00:34:54,593 --> 00:34:56,386
I think it's moved.

610
00:34:56,469 --> 00:35:00,223
-I think it's letting me go.
-I think it's letting me go.

611
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:03,435
DEE DEE: What do you mean?
Letting you go from what?

612
00:35:03,518 --> 00:35:06,771
BIFF: He's repeating now.
He's the one doing it. It's him.

613
00:35:06,855 --> 00:35:08,940
JETHRO: He's separating.

614
00:35:09,024 --> 00:35:12,611
Mrs Silvestry, is that you?

615
00:35:12,861 --> 00:35:16,740
Yes. Yes. It's me.

616
00:35:16,823 --> 00:35:19,993
-Yes. Yes. It's me.
-I'm coming back.

617
00:35:20,076 --> 00:35:24,372
-Listen, it's me.
-I'm coming back. Listen, it's me.

618
00:35:24,456 --> 00:35:26,875
It's like it's passed into the Doctor.
It's transferred.

619
00:35:26,958 --> 00:35:29,669
Whatever it is, it's gone inside him.

620
00:35:30,503 --> 00:35:33,840
No, that's not what happened.

621
00:35:37,969 --> 00:35:39,429
Look at her.

622
00:35:42,015 --> 00:35:43,683
Look at me.

623
00:35:43,767 --> 00:35:45,769
-I can move.
-Look at me.

624
00:35:45,852 --> 00:35:47,312
I can feel again.

625
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:49,606
-I'm coming back to life.
-I can move.

626
00:35:49,731 --> 00:35:50,815
I can feel again.

627
00:35:50,899 --> 00:35:52,567
-And look at him.
-I'm coming back to life.

628
00:35:52,651 --> 00:35:54,736
-He can't move.
-And look at him.

629
00:35:54,819 --> 00:35:56,363
He can't move.

630
00:36:01,493 --> 00:36:03,370
-Help me.
-Help me.

631
00:36:03,453 --> 00:36:05,330
-Professor.
-Professor.

632
00:36:05,413 --> 00:36:08,625
-Get me away from him.
-Get me away from him.

633
00:36:08,708 --> 00:36:10,877
-Please.
-Please.

634
00:36:25,225 --> 00:36:27,560
Oh, thank you!

635
00:36:27,894 --> 00:36:29,854
Oh, thank you!

636
00:36:29,938 --> 00:36:32,524
JETHRO: They've completely separated.
BIFF: It's in him.

637
00:36:32,607 --> 00:36:34,609
Do you see?
I said it was him all the time.

638
00:36:34,693 --> 00:36:37,153
She's free. She's been saved.

639
00:36:37,237 --> 00:36:40,657
-Oh, it was so cold.
-It was so cold.

640
00:36:40,782 --> 00:36:43,243
-I couldn't breathe.
-I couldn't breathe.

641
00:36:43,326 --> 00:36:45,161
-I'm sorry.
-I'm sorry.

642
00:36:45,245 --> 00:36:49,749
-I must have scared you so much.
-I must have scared you so much.

643
00:36:49,833 --> 00:36:51,626
No, it's all right. I've got you.

644
00:36:51,710 --> 00:36:54,295
Oh, there you are, my love. It's gone.

645
00:36:54,379 --> 00:36:56,339
-Everything's all right.
-I wouldn't touch her.

646
00:36:56,423 --> 00:36:58,633
But it's gone. She's clean.
It passed into him.

647
00:36:58,717 --> 00:37:01,845
-That's not what happened.
-Thank you for your opinion, Dee,

648
00:37:01,970 --> 00:37:05,306
but clearly Mrs Silvestry
has been released.

649
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:07,308
-No!
-Just leave her alone.

650
00:37:07,434 --> 00:37:09,352
She's safe, isn't she?

651
00:37:09,936 --> 00:37:14,482
-Jethro, it's let her go, hasn't it?
-Think so, yeah. Looks like it.

652
00:37:15,316 --> 00:37:16,735
Professor?

653
00:37:16,818 --> 00:37:21,740
I'd say, from observation,
the Doctor can't move,

654
00:37:21,823 --> 00:37:24,909
and when she was possessed,
she couldn't move, so...

655
00:37:24,993 --> 00:37:26,870
Well, there we are, then.

656
00:37:28,329 --> 00:37:30,790
Now the only problem
we've got is this Doctor.

657
00:37:31,249 --> 00:37:34,794
-It's inside his head.
-DOCTOR: It's inside his head.

658
00:37:36,087 --> 00:37:38,673
-It killed the driver.
-It killed the driver.

659
00:37:38,757 --> 00:37:41,259
-And the mechanic.
-And the mechanic.

660
00:37:41,342 --> 00:37:44,220
-And now it wants us.
-And now it wants us.

661
00:37:44,304 --> 00:37:45,430
I said so.

662
00:37:45,513 --> 00:37:48,641
-He's waited so long.
-He's waited so long.

663
00:37:48,725 --> 00:37:50,310
-In the dark...
-In the dark...

664
00:37:50,393 --> 00:37:52,395
-...and the cold...
-...and the cold...

665
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:55,148
-...and the diamonds...
-...and the diamonds...

666
00:37:55,231 --> 00:37:57,525
-...until you came.
-...until you came.

667
00:37:57,650 --> 00:38:00,695
-Bodies so hot...
-Bodies so hot...

668
00:38:00,820 --> 00:38:02,697
-...with blood...
-...with blood...

669
00:38:02,781 --> 00:38:03,948
-...and pain.
-...and pain.

670
00:38:04,032 --> 00:38:05,700
God, make him stop.
Someone make him stop.

671
00:38:05,825 --> 00:38:08,244
-But she's saying it!
-And you can shut up!

672
00:38:08,369 --> 00:38:11,164
But it's not him, it's her!
He's just repeating.

673
00:38:11,289 --> 00:38:12,791
But that's what the thing does.
It repeats.

674
00:38:12,874 --> 00:38:14,083
Let her talk.

675
00:38:14,209 --> 00:38:16,669
What do you know?
Fat lot of good you've been.

676
00:38:16,753 --> 00:38:19,297
Just let her explain.

677
00:38:19,380 --> 00:38:22,884
Well, I think,
I mean, from what I've seen,

678
00:38:22,967 --> 00:38:25,970
it repeats, then it synchronises,
then it goes on to the next stage

679
00:38:26,054 --> 00:38:28,056
and that's exactly what
the Doctor said would happen.

680
00:38:28,139 --> 00:38:29,974
-What, and you're on his side?
-No!

681
00:38:30,058 --> 00:38:32,769
JETHRO: The voice is the thing.
DEE DEE: And she's the voice.

682
00:38:32,894 --> 00:38:35,730
She stole it! Look at her.

683
00:38:35,855 --> 00:38:38,066
It's not possessing him,
it's draining him.

684
00:38:38,191 --> 00:38:39,651
She's got his voice.

685
00:38:39,734 --> 00:38:41,986
That's not true 'cause it can't be
"cause I saw it pass into him.

686
00:38:42,070 --> 00:38:43,905
-I saw it with my own eyes.
-So did I.

687
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:46,658
-DEE DEE: You didn't.
-It went from her to him.

688
00:38:46,741 --> 00:38:48,660
-You saw it, didn't you?
-I don't know.

689
00:38:48,743 --> 00:38:51,204
VAL: Oh, don't be stupid, Jethro!
Of course you did!

690
00:38:51,287 --> 00:38:53,581
-I suppose he was right next to her.
-Everyone saw it! Everyone!

691
00:38:53,706 --> 00:38:55,750
You're just making it up.

692
00:38:55,834 --> 00:38:59,504
I know what I saw
and I saw her stealing his voice.

693
00:38:59,587 --> 00:39:01,548
She's as bad as him.
Someone shut her up.

694
00:39:01,631 --> 00:39:03,633
-I think you should be quiet, Dee Dee.
-I'm only saying...

695
00:39:03,716 --> 00:39:05,635
And that's an order!

696
00:39:05,718 --> 00:39:09,848
You're making a fool of yourself,
pretending you're an expert in mechanics

697
00:39:09,931 --> 00:39:12,267
and hydraulics when I can tell you,

698
00:39:12,392 --> 00:39:15,562
you are nothing
more than average at best.

699
00:39:15,645 --> 00:39:17,480
Now shut up!

700
00:39:17,564 --> 00:39:19,899
-That's how he does it.
-That's how he does it.

701
00:39:19,983 --> 00:39:22,277
-He makes you fight.
-He makes you fight.

702
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:25,488
-Creeps into your head...
-Creeps into your head...

703
00:39:25,613 --> 00:39:27,866
-...and whispers.
-...and whispers.

704
00:39:27,949 --> 00:39:29,409
-Listen.
-Listen.

705
00:39:29,492 --> 00:39:31,244
-Just listen.
-Just listen.

706
00:39:31,327 --> 00:39:33,204
-That's him.
-That's him.

707
00:39:33,288 --> 00:39:34,873
-Inside.
-Inside.

708
00:39:34,956 --> 00:39:36,708
BIFF: Throw him out.
VAL: Get him out of my head!

709
00:39:36,791 --> 00:39:37,959
We should throw him out.

710
00:39:38,042 --> 00:39:40,253
Don't just talk about it.
Just... You're useless!

711
00:39:40,336 --> 00:39:41,796
-Do something!
-I will!

712
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:44,007
You watch me.
I'm going to throw him out.

713
00:39:44,132 --> 00:39:45,550
-Yes!
-Yes!

714
00:39:45,633 --> 00:39:47,302
-Throw him out!
-Throw him out!

715
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:49,596
-Get rid of him!
-Get rid of him!

716
00:39:49,679 --> 00:39:51,306
-Now!
-Now!

717
00:39:53,224 --> 00:39:55,310
-Don't!
-It'll be you next.

718
00:39:56,185 --> 00:39:57,770
I don't think we should do this.

719
00:39:57,854 --> 00:40:02,233
-It was your idea. Professor, help me.
-I can't...

720
00:40:02,317 --> 00:40:04,235
What sort of a man are you? Come on!

721
00:40:04,319 --> 00:40:05,737
-Throw him out!
-Come on!

722
00:40:05,820 --> 00:40:08,031
Just do it! Throw him out!

723
00:40:08,114 --> 00:40:09,657
-Professor, help me!
-Get him out!

724
00:40:09,741 --> 00:40:11,784
Grab hold of him!
Not like that! Are you stupid?

725
00:40:11,868 --> 00:40:13,953
-Cast him out.
-Cast him out.

726
00:40:14,037 --> 00:40:15,830
-Into the sun.
-Into the sun.

727
00:40:15,914 --> 00:40:17,165
I want him out!

728
00:40:17,248 --> 00:40:19,292
-And the night.
-And the night.

729
00:40:19,375 --> 00:40:21,377
Help me! Get him out!

730
00:40:21,502 --> 00:40:23,046
(ALL SHOUTING)

731
00:40:24,547 --> 00:40:25,798
-Get him out!
-Do it!

732
00:40:25,882 --> 00:40:27,550
-Do it.
-Do it now.

733
00:40:27,634 --> 00:40:29,552
-Do it now.
-Faster.

734
00:40:29,677 --> 00:40:31,346
-Faster.
-Just do it!

735
00:40:31,429 --> 00:40:33,973
-That's the way.
-That's the way.

736
00:40:34,057 --> 00:40:36,434
-You can do it.
-You can do it.

737
00:40:37,060 --> 00:40:39,187
Motto bene!

738
00:40:39,604 --> 00:40:41,731
-Throw him out!
-Motto bene!

739
00:40:41,856 --> 00:40:44,317
-Get him out!
-Allons-y.

740
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:45,902
Allons-y.

741
00:40:46,027 --> 00:40:48,905
-That's his voice!
-The starlight waits!

742
00:40:49,030 --> 00:40:50,448
It's taken his voice!

743
00:40:50,531 --> 00:40:52,951
-The emptiness.
-Get him out!

744
00:40:53,034 --> 00:40:56,704
-The Midnight sky.
-The Midnight sky.

745
00:40:56,829 --> 00:40:58,373
It's her.

746
00:41:01,542 --> 00:41:04,253
-Throw him out!
-Get him out!

747
00:41:04,379 --> 00:41:06,255
She's taken his voice!

748
00:41:10,009 --> 00:41:15,765
One, two, three, four, five, six...

749
00:41:21,229 --> 00:41:23,231
It's gone. It's gone.

750
00:41:24,899 --> 00:41:27,193
It's gone. It's gone. It's gone.

751
00:41:27,276 --> 00:41:29,529
It's gone. It's gone.

752
00:41:32,907 --> 00:41:35,201
It's gone. It's gone. It's gone.

753
00:41:35,284 --> 00:41:37,203
It's gone. It's gone.

754
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:16,993
I said it was her.

755
00:42:38,848 --> 00:42:41,392
WOMAN: Repeat, Crusader 50,

756
00:42:41,476 --> 00:42:44,979
rescue vehicle coming alongside
in three minutes.

757
00:42:45,104 --> 00:42:47,940
Door seals set to automatic.

758
00:42:48,024 --> 00:42:52,320
Prepare for boarding.
Repeat, prepare for boarding.

759
00:42:53,821 --> 00:42:55,281
The hostess.

760
00:42:57,617 --> 00:42:59,368
What was her name?

761
00:43:10,171 --> 00:43:11,672
I don't know.

762
00:43:45,665 --> 00:43:48,084
DONNA: What do you think it was?

763
00:43:49,919 --> 00:43:51,212
No idea.

764
00:43:52,380 --> 00:43:55,007
Do you think it's still out there?

765
00:43:58,302 --> 00:44:01,639
Well, you'd better tell them, this lot.

766
00:44:01,722 --> 00:44:05,226
Yeah. They can build
a Leisure Palace somewhere else.

767
00:44:05,852 --> 00:44:09,689
Let this planet keep on turning
round an extonic star,

768
00:44:10,648 --> 00:44:12,108
in silence.

769
00:44:14,152 --> 00:44:16,737
Can't imagine you without a voice.

770
00:44:17,530 --> 00:44:18,990
Motto bene.

771
00:44:20,199 --> 00:44:21,659
Motto bene.

772
00:44:22,118 --> 00:44:23,911
No. Don't do that.

773
00:44:25,746 --> 00:44:26,998
Don't.

774
00:44:30,459 --> 00:44:31,752
Don't.

775
00:44:38,885 --> 00:44:40,136
Found a body, sir.

776
00:44:40,219 --> 00:44:41,470
The Doctor is dead.

777
00:44:41,554 --> 00:44:44,223
How could anything be worse than this?

778
00:44:44,307 --> 00:44:46,309
What happened? What did they find?

779
00:44:46,434 --> 00:44:49,061
Oh, my God. The stars are going out.

780
00:44:49,187 --> 00:44:51,856
-Who are you?
-I was like you.

781
00:44:51,939 --> 00:44:53,608
Turn around! Show me your face!

782
00:44:53,691 --> 00:44:56,277
I've been pulled across
from a different universe

783
00:44:56,360 --> 00:44:58,362
'cause every single universe
is in danger.

784
00:44:58,446 --> 00:45:00,907
There's something on your back!

785
00:45:01,240 --> 00:45:03,201
What am I supposed to do?

786
00:45:03,284 --> 00:45:04,785
Powering up!

787
00:45:05,119 --> 00:45:07,121
None of this is meant to happen.

788
00:45:07,246 --> 00:45:09,081
You're going to die.

